hands_on_practices.solution:
Below threshold steady‐state photon number $ \bar n_{below} $ satisfies
$$0=(G_{amp}-\gamma_c)\bar n_{below}+R_{sp}
\quad\Rightarrow\quad
\bar n_{below}=\frac{R_{sp}}{\gamma_c-G_{amp}}.$$
Hence
$$P_{below}=\bar n_{below}h\nu\,\gamma_c
=\frac{R_{sp}}{\gamma_c-G_{amp}}\,h\nu\,\gamma_c.$$
The ASE linewidth is
$$\Delta\nu_{ASE}=\frac{\gamma_c-G_{amp}}{2\pi}$$
so the below‐threshold product is
$$\Pi_{below}
=\Delta\nu_{ASE}P_{below}
=\frac{\gamma_c-G_{amp}}{2\pi}
\cdot\frac{R_{sp}h\nu\,\gamma_c}{\gamma_c-G_{amp}}
=\frac{R_{sp}h\nu\,\gamma_c}{2\pi}.$$

Above threshold $G_{amp}=\gamma_c$ and steady‐state $\bar n_{above}$ yields
$$P_{above}=\bar n_{above}h\nu\,\gamma_c.$$
The STH linewidth is
$$\Delta\nu_{STH}=\frac{R_{sp}(1+\alpha^2)}{4\pi\bar n_{above}}$$
giving
$$\Pi_{above}
=\Delta\nu_{STH}P_{above}
=\frac{R_{sp}(1+\alpha^2)}{4\pi\bar n_{above}}
\cdot\bar n_{above}h\nu\,\gamma_c
=\frac{R_{sp}(1+\alpha^2)h\nu\,\gamma_c}{4\pi}.$$

Thus the ratio is
$$
\mathcal R=\frac{\Pi_{above}}{\Pi_{below}}
=\frac{\displaystyle\frac{R_{sp}(1+\alpha^2)h\nu\,\gamma_c}{4\pi}}
{\displaystyle\frac{R_{sp}h\nu\,\gamma_c}{2\pi}}
=\frac{1+\alpha^2}{4\pi}\,\frac{2\pi}{1}
=\frac{1+\alpha^2}{2}\,. $$
